#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:13
msgid ""
"*Meta* objects are *implicit surfaces*, meaning that they are *not "
"explicitly* defined by vertices (as meshes are) or control points (as "
"surfaces are): they exist *procedurally*. Meta objects are literally "
"mathematical formulas that are calculated on-the-fly by Blender."
msgstr ""
"*融球* 物体是 *隐式表面*，这意味着它们 *不是明确* 由顶点(如网格)或控制点(如曲"
"面)定义的：它们只是在 *程序上* 存在着。融球物体实际上是由Blender即时计算的数学公"
"式。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:18
msgid ""
"A very distinct visual characteristic of metas is that they are fluid "
"*mercurial*, or *clay-like* forms that have a \"rounded\" shape. "
"Furthermore, when two meta objects get close to one another, they begin to "
"interact with one another. They \"blend\" or \"merge\", as water droplets "
"do, especially in zero-g (which, by the way, makes them very handy for "
"modeling streams of water when you do not want to do a fluid simulation). If "
"they subsequently move away from one another, they restore their original "
"shape."
msgstr ""
"融球的一个非常独特的视觉特征是它们是具有“圆形”形状的流动的 *水银状*，或者的 *"
"粘土状* 形式。 此外，当两个融球物体彼此靠近时，它们开始彼此交融。特别是在零重"
"力时，它们像水滴一样“混合”或“融合”(顺便一提，当不想进行流体模拟时，它们非常便"
"于模拟水流)。 如果它们随后彼此远离，它们会恢复原来的形状。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:25
msgid ""
"Each of these is defined by its own underlying mathematical :doc:`structure "
"</modeling/metas/structure>`, and you can at any time switch between them "
"using the *Active Element* panel."
msgstr ""
"每个都由它自己的底层数学 :doc:`结构 </modeling/metas/structure>` 定义，可以随"
"时使用 *活动元素* 面板在它们之间切换。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:28
msgid ""
"Typically *Meta* objects are used for special effects or as a basis for "
"modeling. For example, you could use a collection of metas to form the "
"initial shape of your model and then convert it to a mesh for further "
"modeling or sculpting. Meta objects are also very efficient for ray tracing."
msgstr ""
"通常， *融球* 物体用于特殊效果或作为建模的基础。例如，您可以使用一组融球来形"
"成模型的初始形状，然后将其转换为网格，以便进行进一步建模或雕刻。融球对于光线"
"跟踪也非常有效。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/metas/introduction.rst:34
msgid ""
"Names of *Meta* objects are very important, as they define :ref:`families "
"<meta-ball-object-families>`, and only objects within a same family interact "
"with each other. Unlike other object types, even edition (transformations) "
"in Object Mode will affect the generated geometry within the edited families."
msgstr ""
"*融球* 物体的名称非常重要，因为它们定义了 :ref:`族 <meta-ball-object-"
"families>` ，并且只有在同一个族内的物体才彼此交互。与其他物体类型不同，即使是"
"物体模式下的编辑(转换)也会影响已编辑的族内生成的几何图形。"

